US GOVERNMENT TELEPHONE INTERCEPT: 24 JUNE 2008A phone call was intercepted from a pay phone at the Domodedovo International Airport to a street phone in Nonthaburi on June 24, 2008.  The call on June 24, 2008 was from Arkadi Borodinski to Boonmee Khemkhaeng or Suramongkol Virote.  The caller says [in English with a Russian accent]: “I am encouraged by what I hear from my sources about you.”  The receiver replies [also in English]: “I hope we can do business shortly.” 